 ng ou ni nj nk ov nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"bdad\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Overview</strong>: Global News headlines were also analyzed.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"6562\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Structure</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">X-Axis</strong>: Timeline from 2023 to 2024. \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Y-Axis</strong>: Sentiment values fluctuating between <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.25</strong> and <strong class=\"mt gr\">0.05</strong>.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"8e94\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Observations</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Mean Sentiment</strong>: Approximately <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.12</strong>, making it the least negative among the three sources. \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Median Sentiment</strong>: Close to <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.12</strong>, indicating consistent sentiment. \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Trend Line</strong>: Shows a slightly concave trajectory, peaking mid-way and dipping back.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"36e4\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Insight</strong>: While Global News\u2019 sentiment scores fluctuate, the overall trend suggests slightly less negativity than the other sources.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nt nu gq bg nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bl\" id=\"f01a\">Sentiment on Holidays</h2><figure class=\"pw px py pz qa mf lx ly paragraph-image\"><div class=\"mg mh eo mi bi mj\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"lx ly qb\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 1400w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*6yIyVt9NzOpCvkVFgZHHOQ.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lh mk c\" height=\"467\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div></figure><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"8c25\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Overview</strong>: The compound sentiment scores on various Canadian holidays were compared across the three news sources.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"472c\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Structure</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Y-Axis</strong>: List of holidays from <strong class=\"mt gr\">Discovery Day</strong> (2023\u201308\u201319) to <strong class=\"mt gr\">Labour Day</strong> (2024\u201309\u201302). \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">X-Axis</strong>: Sentiment scores ranging from <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.25</strong> to <strong class=\"mt gr\">0.05</strong>.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"feb0\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Observations</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Average Holiday Sentiment Scores</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">CBC</strong>: <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.11</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">CTV</strong>: <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.10</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Global</strong>: <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.07</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Global News</strong> consistently reported with a slightly more positive tone on holidays, especially on <strong class=\"mt gr\">Boxing Day</strong> and <strong class=\"mt gr\">Canada Day</strong>.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"0943\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Insight</strong>: Global News may adopt a more positive editorial stance during holidays compared to CBC and CTV.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nt nu gq bg nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bl\" id=\"d1be\">Average Sentiment by Weekday</h2><figure class=\"pw px py pz qa mf lx ly paragraph-image\"><div class=\"mg mh eo mi bi mj\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"lx ly qc\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 1400w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*aut0bFmqL0SUT29cIN3dyA.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lh mk c\" height=\"467\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div></figure><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"a433\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Overview</strong>: The average sentiment scores were calculated for each weekday to identify any patterns.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"0a0f\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Structure</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Y-Axis</strong>: Days of the week (Monday to Sunday). \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">X-Axis</strong>: Sentiment scores between <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.16</strong> and <strong class=\"mt gr\">0</strong>.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"7222\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Observations</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Average Weekday Sentiment Scores</strong>: \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">CBC</strong>: Mean around <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.13</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">CTV</strong>: Mean around <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.14</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Global</strong>: Mean around <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.12</strong> \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Mondays</strong>: Showed slightly more negative sentiment across all sources, with average scores around <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.14</strong> to <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.16</strong>. \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Saturdays</strong>: Had less negativity, with scores closer to <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.12</strong>. \u2014 <strong class=\"mt gr\">Global News</strong> remained the least negative on most weekdays.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"9ced\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Insight</strong>: Sentiment is slightly more negative on Mondays across all sources, while Saturdays show less negativity, suggesting a potential weekend effect on news tone.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nt nu gq bg nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bl\" id=\"da15\">Interpretation of Findings</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mr ms gq mt b mu or mw mx my os na nb nc ot ne nf ng ou ni nj nk ov nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"2bc0\">The analyses reveal subtle differences in the sentiment trends among the three major Canadian news outlets:</p><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"4fee\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Overall Negativity</strong>: All three sources exhibited a generally negative tone in their headlines, with compound sentiment scores averaging between <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.12</strong> and <strong class=\"mt gr\">-0.14</strong>.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"dfaa\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Positive Trends</strong>: There is a slight upward trend in sentiment scores over time, indicating a gradual shift towards less negative or more neutral headlines.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"99b5\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Source Comparison</strong>: Global News tends to have a slightly less negative tone compared to CBC and CTV, both over time and on specific occasions like holidays.</li><li class=\"mr ms gq mt b mu oz mw mx my pa na nb nc pb ne nf ng pc ni nj nk pd nm nn no ow ox oy bl\" id=\"4556\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">Weekday Variations</strong>: Sentiment scores fluctuate slightly throughout the week, with Mondays being more negative and weekends showing less negativity. These findings suggest that while Canadian news outlets maintain a generally negative tone \u2014 perhaps due to the nature of news reporting \u2014 there are variations based on the source, time, and specific events like holidays.</li></ul><h2 class=\"nt nu gq bg nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bl\" id=\"9f9c\">Conclusion</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mr ms gq mt b mu or mw mx my os na nb nc ot ne nf ng ou ni nj nk ov nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"772b\">By systematically collecting, processing, and analyzing headline data from major news outlets, the project highlighted subtle shifts in media tone and offered a unique perspective on how news sentiment varies over time and across different sources. While the project focused on headlines \u2014 which are designed to grab attention and may not fully represent the content of the articles \u2014 the findings suggest that news outlets maintain consistent editorial tones, with slight variations influenced by time and events. For those interested in exploring the data further or conducting their own analyses, I\u2019ve uploaded all collected data (including logged headlines) to the <a class=\"ah mq\" href=\"https://github.com/kmaurinjones/DailyNewsDriftCanada/tree/main/data\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">project\u2019s repository</a>.</p><h2 class=\"nt nu gq bg nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on oo op oq bl\" id=\"23b7\">Final Thoughts</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mr ms gq mt b mu or mw mx my os na nb nc ot ne nf ng ou ni nj nk ov nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"cfbc\">Developing DailyNewsDriftCanada has been an enlightening experience, blending data science, natural language processing, and media analysis. The project demonstrates how technology can be harnessed to make sense of large amounts of textual data and uncover meaningful patterns in media sentiment. I hope this exploration provides a clear understanding of the conceptual aspects of the pipeline and the insights gained from the analyses.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mr ms gq mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"cdc4\">If you have any questions or feedback, feel free to reach out! at</p><blockquote class=\"nq nr ns\"><p class=\"mr ms np mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"498b\">LinkedIn: <a class=\"ah mq\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><strong class=\"mt gr\">https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/</strong></a></p></blockquote><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph mr ms gq mt b mu mv mw mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk nl nm nn no gj bl\" id=\"4fa5\">Thank you for reading!</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article>"}
